replies.text:
@ThinkingandTinkering I imagine it would be really tricky, and of course you would have to carefully grow the plants into the device [like hope all of the roots follow special nutrient filled tubes of some sort so you can work around them and stuff without getting so large they break the device they are in... Might would need a flexible membrane for a tube like a fluoroelastomer,  might prove financially/commercially unfeasible, but imagine how much power density one could store if they could somehow store the protons of hydrogen in one cavity and the electrons in the other, and just let them mix as you needed electrical power. The theoretical energy density would be [literally] on the atomic level! [because of it being stripped down hydrogen atoms I mean] 

I imagine it would be insanely hard to collect and/or store, or somebody would have already done it by now.

Still, I write about it in one of my sci-fi stories as a well developed type of power storage for the characters.
